modules.description: This module defines data structures for representing timelines, including dates with optional precision, textual content, media elements, slides, and eras. It supports building rich, interactive timelines with structured data for display in a visualization library. Concrete use cases include constructing historical timelines with media, captions, and background styling, as well as organizing events into groups with optional time ranges and display formatting.

This module creates and configures interactive timelines with customizable display options like height, width, zoom levels, and localization settings. It supports data structures for events, media, and dates, allowing precise control over timeline content and appearance. Concrete use cases include embedding historical event timelines, interactive storytelling, and data-driven visual chronologies directly in web applications.

This module constructs timeline data structures with precise date handling, text formatting, media embedding, and slide/era organization. It supports creating rich interactive timelines with customizable display properties and hierarchical grouping. Concrete use cases include building historical timelines, event sequences, and annotated media-rich chronological displays.

This module defines JSON encodings for timeline-related data structures, including dates, text, media, slides, eras, and full timelines. It works directly with the data types from `Ezjs_timeline.Timeline_types` to serialize and deserialize timeline content. Concrete use cases include converting timeline data to and from JSON for storage, transmission, or integration with web services.

This module implements interactive timelines with customizable display options, supporting data structures for events, media, and dates. It provides operations for creating, encoding, and organizing timeline content with precise date handling and localization. Concrete use cases include embedding historical event timelines, interactive storytelling, and data-driven chronologies in web applications.
